snippet.title: EA SPORTS FC 26 | Official Gameplay Deep Dive
snippet.description:
Play your way in FC 26 with overhauled gameplay, powered by community feedback. Pre-order FC 26 now: https://x.ea.com/84938

For a more in depth breakdown check out the full Pitch Notes here: https://x.ea.com/85015

EA SPORTS FC™ 26 brings more responsive dribbling, smarter AI positioning, and sharper, more explosive movement — all based on community feedback. Goalkeepers now react more naturally with improved positioning, animations are more lifelike, and new Playstyles and Player Roles give you more ways to shape how your team plays. Learn more https://x.ea.com/85016

Pre-order EA SPORTS FC 26™ Ultimate Edition by August 26 to receive an untradeable ICON Player Item as soon as you start playing the game. At a later date, it will become an upgraded version to recognize the moment they became a Champion.

EA SPORTS FC 25™ players will also receive an EVO that boosts any player’s shooting to 99 and Pick 1 of 5 untradeable ICON players rated 93+ from previous campaigns including Grassroot Greats, FUT Birthday, Dreamchasers & FUT Immortals in EA SPORTS FC™ 25: https://x.ea.com/84938

0:00 - Intro

3:03 - Gameplay Fundamentals

snippet.title: Predator: Badlands | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
First hunt. Last chance.

From the director of Prey, watch the brand-new trailer for Predator: Badlands, in theaters November 7.

“Predator: Badlands,” which stars Elle Fanning and Dimitrius Schuster-Koloamatangi, is set in the future on a remote planet, where a young Predator, outcast from his clan, finds an unlikely ally in Thia (Fanning) and embarks on a treacherous journey in search of the ultimate adversary. The film is directed by Dan Trachtenberg and produced by John Davis, Dan Trachtenberg, Marc Toberoff, Ben Rosenblatt, Brent O’Connor.

snippet.title: Standing on Business with Love Island's Chelley and Olandria
snippet.description:
We’ve got a text… and it’s from two of Live Island’s most unforgettable OGs, Chelley and Olandria. In their first post-Love Island interview together, they’re pulling no punches. From navigating double standards as Black women to clearing up the rumors, were Chelley and Ace dating before the villa? And how did Nicolandria go from unexpected to iconic? Olandria spills on Taylor, Clarke, Nic, and a few heads that may have turned. They also break down the real story behind the six-hour Stand on Business challenge and what it’s like being labeled “mean girls” just for keeping it real. It’s a full-on villa recoupling, don’t miss it!

Keke Palmer has questions for days, about everything under the sun. From the existential to the inconsequential, and everything in between. And now she’s diving into the brains of entertainment’s best and brightest to get some answers. From Snoop Dogg to Jordan Peele to Quinta Brunson, to John Stamos, Keke is getting to the bottom of the burning topics that keep us up at night. This is Keke as her most authentic self, going all in on everything in her life and the lives of her celeb guests, because Baby, this is Keke Palmer, and she is here for All. Of. It. You know it’s your girl!

snippet.description:
She scatters dewdrops upon every bloom,
And tints the twilight with a sheen of silver.

Thus do shadows howl across the gloomy woods,
As flocks of deer and birds take fright and shiver.

She hums one nameless tune,
While walking through those solitary halls.

So her homeland may not fall to desolation,
So the tale may not be lost to oblivion.

snippet.title: Gyokeres? We need MORE PLAYERS | Mikel Arteta | Arsenal in Asia
snippet.description:
Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta updates progress on the club's pursuit of Viktor Gyokeres and other transfer targets on the first day of their pre-season tour of Singapore.

TIMESTAMPS
0:00 INTRO
0:05 excited about new season after great training with new signings in Spain. Adapting to weather and unable to train this morning
0:45 new signings like 'shaking the tree' and bring new energy - heights need to go to a new level
1:10 players are convinced how good they are and ready to take the next step.
1:58 Zubimendi? a long process and he could have gone elsewhere but he wanted to come to Arsenal and we are all so impressed now we have seen him in training.
2:49 Gyokeres? Can't comment on player who is not part of our group yet
3:10 four signings already - can we expect more players to sign and come to Singapore? Still a long time to go and we are still short on numbers
3:40 Who can get into first team from young players? Whoever knocks down the door - up to them
4:08 Partey charges reaction? club has been clear that legal matters mean I can not comments
4:40 confident club followed right processes? 100 per cent 
4:57 Calafiori expectations for his second season?  his injuries last season were on international duty with Italy and now we want him consistently available.
6:01 changes since you played in Singapore with Arsenal ten years ago? our supporters here are v passionate and we want to connect with them.
7:11 ten years ago I did not expect to be sitting here (as manager) 
7:50 four players in still hopes we can improve the team
8:33 I am pleased with where we are so far in the transfer window and hopeful there will be more very soon
8:52 window has been exciting as seen ambition club has throughout the club
9:11 Gabriel be fit for new season? He is committed and has a new contract and played 45 minutes against Watford at weekend and looks in good shape 
10:02 Madueke - why so many Chelsea players? They have a lot of great players and we focus on who we want rather than the club they are in. he is having a break aftyer winning the Club World Cup and the players who know him are delighted we have signed him.
